    "Ramponi and Casula [2023a] present a benchmark dataset for dialects of Italian.",
    "The benchmark is named as DIATOPIT.",
    "There has been recent work on creating a corpus of Norwegian dialect [Barnes et al. 2021].",
    "Also, Alshutayri and Atwell [2018] present a large (200K+ instances) corpus for Arabic dialects and Standard Arabic.",
    "The data is sourced largely from tweets but also includes comments from newspapers, and Facebook."
